    "solution": {
      "final_answer": "18",
      "explanation": {
        "concept": "Use identity: (x + 1/x)^3 = x^3 + 1/x^3 + 3(x + 1/x)",
        "step_by_step": [
          "Given x + 1/x = 3",
          "Cube both sides: (x + 1/x)^3 = 27",
          "Use identity: x^3 + 1/x^3 + 3(x + 1/x) = 27",
          "Substitute: x^3 + 1/x^3 + 3(3) = 27",
          "x^3 + 1/x^3 + 9 = 27",
          "x^3 + 1/x^3 = 18"
        ],
        "why_correct": {
